text: The Division of Cowper is an Australian electoral division in New South Wales. It was one of 75 divisions set up for the first federal election in 1901. It is named for Charles Cowper, an early Premier of New South Wales. It is on the north coast of New South Wales, and includes the towns of Coffs Harbour, Kempsey, Macksville, Nambucca Heads and Port Macquarie. ==Members== Member Party Term Francis Clarke Protectionist 1901–1903 Henry Lee Free Trade, Anti-Socialist 1903–1906 John Thomson Protectionist [1906–1909 Commonwealth Liberal 1909–1917 Nationalist 1917–1919 (Sir) Earle Page Country 1919–1961 Frank McGuren Labor 1961–1963 Ian Robinson Country 1963–1975 National Country 1975–1982 National 1982–1984 Garry Nehl National 1984–2001 Luke Hartsuyker National 2001–present Its most famous member was Sir Earle Page, leader of the Country Party and Prime Minister of Australia in 1939. ==Election results== ==References== ==Other websites== * Australian Electoral Commission * Luke Hartsuyker's website Category:Electoral divisions of New South Wales Category:1901 establishments in Australia
